- `getActiveBits()` returns the maximum number of bits needed to represent any value in the range (unsigned interpretation)
- `getMinSignedBits()` returns the maximum of `getSignificantBits()` for the signed min and max values in the range

For `trunc nuw`: The result is poison if any truncated bits are non-zero. This means the value must fit in the destination width when interpreted as unsigned.

For `trunc nsw`: The result is poison if any truncated bits are not the same as the top bit of the truncation result. This means the value must fit in the destination width when interpreted as signed.

